SUMMARY:The Swapanistas Present: Swap! A Women's Clothing Exchange
DTSTAMP:20260308T025022Z
DTSTART:20260314T100000Z
DESCRIPTION:Are you ready to swap up your style? \\nThen join us for Swap 2
	026! \\nSwap is an amazing event where you let go of your gently used clot
	hing and accessories and trade them in for items that make you feel brand 
	new\\\, while having fun and supporting a good cause: proceeds and clothin
	g donations benefit local organizations for underserved women and kids. \\
	nWe are excited to announce that this year’s event is being hosted in part
	nership with the Phinney Neighborhood Association\\\, truly making this a 
	community event! \\n​​Come check it out\\\, and bring your friends! \\nSwa
	p: Saturday March 14th\\\, 10 AM – 1:30 PM\\nItem Drop-off: Friday March 1
	3th\\\, 5 PM – 8 PM \\nFor tickets and more info\\\, please visit our webs
	ite: https://www.swapanistas.org/ \\nPlease email us with questions: swapa
	nistas@gmail.com \\nHope to see you there!\n\nhttps://myballard.com/event/
	the-swapanistas-present-swap-a-womens-clothing-exchange/\n\nFrom My Ballar
	d
URL:https://myballard.com/event/the-swapanistas-present-swap-a-womens-cloth
	ing-exchange/
LOCATION:Phinney Neighborhood Center\\\, 6532 Phinney Ave N Room 7\\\, Seat
	tle\\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:myballard
CATEGORIES:My Ballard
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:mYJ4xm3tMq-1WLLF6Fp-x
SUMMARY:Art Class: Nature Journaling & basics of making botanical Inks
DTSTAMP:20260308T025022Z
DTSTART:20260314T130000Z
DESCRIPTION:Pause and see the natural world more closely through nature jou
	rnaling and botanical inks. In this gentle\\\, hands-on class\\\, you’ll l
	earn the basics of making ink from flowers and use these plant-based pigme
	nts to start a nature journal. You’ll also learn how considerations like p
	aper and additives can give you different and exciting colors. All materia
	ls are included and each participant will take home a small sketchbook tha
	t we make in class and a 15ml pot of handmade floral ink—an invitation to 
	notice new growth\\\, returning light\\\, and the unfolding of spring.\n\n
	https://myballard.com/event/art-class-nature-journaling-basics-of-making-b
	otanical-inks/\n\nFrom My Ballard
URL:https://myballard.com/event/art-class-nature-journaling-basics-of-makin
	g-botanical-inks/
LOCATION:Swoon City\\\, 1716 NW Market St\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98107\\\, 
	United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:myballard
CATEGORIES:My Ballard
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
