BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:c_xs-jOt-CJjhvkS3cYuw
SUMMARY:Embroidery Class: Sashiko Tea Towel Workshop
DTSTAMP:20260308T025022Z
DTSTART:20260425T103000Z
DESCRIPTION:Learn the basics of Japanese sashiko hand stitching and apply i
	t to embellish a tea towel.\\nSashiko is a Japanese running stitch traditi
	onally used to mend and strengthen textiles and clothing\\\, as well as cr
	eating geometric patterns. \\nIn this hands-on 2 hour workshop\\\, learn t
	he basics of Japanese sashiko stitching and apply it to embellish a tea to
	wel.\\nYou will learn how to work with sashiko needles and thread and sew 
	a running stitch. \\nEach student will take home a set of sashiko needles\
	\\, 2 skeins of sashiko thread\\\, and a cotton tea towel. \\nSashiko is a
	n excellent way to slow down and stitch with mindfulness. There is such be
	auty in its imperfection and its simplicity\\\, flexibility and adaptabili
	ty to many projects! \\nThis workshop is for sewers of all levels\\\, from
	 beginners to experienced. \\nThis class will take place at Swoon City.\n\
	nhttps://myballard.com/event/embroidery-class-sashiko-tea-towel-workshop/\
	n\nFrom My Ballard
URL:https://myballard.com/event/embroidery-class-sashiko-tea-towel-workshop
	/
LOCATION:Swoon City\\\, 1716 NW Market St\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98107\\\, 
	United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:myballard
CATEGORIES:My Ballard
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
